																								 New Delhi, Dec. 3: Direct tax collections grew 44.86 per cent during April-November this year to Rs 1,45,053 crore from Rs 1,00,135 crore in the year-ago period. Net direct tax collections have continued to grow at over 40 per cent and the government has succeeded in achieving over 54 per cent of budgeted direct tax target of Rs 2,67,490 crore in the first eight months, a finance ministry statement said.																								 New Delhi, Dec. 3: A group of ministers, constituted to look into the pricing of petroleum products, will meet on December 7 for the first time.																								 New Delhi, Dec. 3: Corporate Indias business confidence index has increased to 146 points for the second quarter this fiscal against 137.9 points in the previous quarter, NCAER said in its quarterly review.																								 New Delhi, Dec. 3: The UAEs state-run realty firm Rakeen will invest up to $5 billion in Indias realty market along with local partner Trimex Group over the next five years. The partners have formed a joint venture, Rakiendo Developers.																								 Calcutta, Dec. 3: Indian Jute Manufacturers Association has asked its member mills to pay an advance bonus to avoid a token strike on Wednesday.
